note.p:
Pub. L. 116–315, title V, § 5401, Jan. 5, 2021, 134 Stat. 5045, provided that: “The Secretary of Veterans Affairs shall— “(1) collect and analyze data on each program of the Department of Veterans Affairs that provides a service or benefit to a veteran, including the program carried out under section 1144 of title 10, United States Code;
“(2) disaggregate such data by gender, race, and ethnicity, when the data lends itself to such disaggregation; and
“(3) publish the data collected and analyzed under paragraph (1), except for such cases in which the Secretary determines that some portions of the data would undermine the anonymity of a veteran.”
